    • Method Detail

      • execute

        public java.lang.String execute()
        Displays a venue's list of sections given the that is logged in is a venue user. Otherwise the no permission page is displayed.
        Specified by:
        execute in interface com.opensymphony.xwork2.Action
        Overrides:
        execute in class com.opensymphony.xwork2.ActionSupport
        Returns:
        Success if user passes login check, otherwise permission_error.

      • NewSection

        public java.lang.String NewSection()
        Displays the page that allows the venue user to add a new section to their menu.
        Returns:
        Success if user passes login check otherwise permission_error.

      • InsertSection

        public java.lang.String InsertSection()
        Takes value description from jsp file and passes it along with the venueid of the user to ConnectionManager.getVenueID(). This adds the section to the database.
        Returns:
        SUCCESS if operation is successfully otherwise return db_error. If user login is not valid return permission_error.

      • DeleteSection

        public java.lang.String DeleteSection()
        This method gets the values from the jsp that have been selected for deletion and passes them into the DeleteSections method in ConnectionManager.This method will then carry out the required processes to delete the section(s). If no sections have been selected for deletion the function will return an error
        Returns:
        ERROR if no item has been selected for deletion. SUCCESS if a section has been selected. "permission_error" if the user trying to access the method is not the valid venue owner.

      • EditSection

        public java.lang.String EditSection()
        Gets the ID of the section that has been selected to edit by the user and populates the jsp file with it's current properties so the user can make changes. "Name" is used to pass the name of the section into the jsp.
        Returns:
        SUCCESS if the fetch from the database was successful. db_error if it was not. permission_error if the user currently logged in is not valid.

      • UpdateSection

        public java.lang.String UpdateSection()
        Update section given the changes the user made in the page generated in the EditSection() method.
        Returns:
        SUCCESS if the update was a success. db_error if it was a fail. permission_error if the user is not valid.

      • DisplayItems

        public java.lang.String DisplayItems()
        Displays the items belonging to the section that the user has selected. Passes the sectionID into ConnectionManager.getItemsBySection() which returns a map contained all the items. JSP iterates through the map to display the items.
        Returns:
        SUCCESS if operation is successful. permission_error if user is invalid.

      • NewItem

        public java.lang.String NewItem()
        Displays the page that allows the venue user to add a new item to their section.
        Returns:
        Success if user passes login check otherwise permission_error.

      • InsertItem

        public java.lang.String InsertItem()
        Insert a new item to the database with the values the user has filled into the fields in the jsp file.
        Returns:
        SUCCESS if the operation was a success. db_error if it failed. permission_error if the user is not valid.

      • DeleteItem

        public java.lang.String DeleteItem()
        This method gets the values from the jsp that have been selected for deletion and passes them into the DeleteItems method in ConnectionManager.This method will then carry out the required processes to delete the item(s). If no items have been selected for deletion the function will return an error
        Returns:
        ERROR if no item has been selected for deletion. SUCCESS if a item has been selected. "permission_error" if the user trying to access the method is not the valid venue owner.

      • EditItem

        public java.lang.String EditItem()
        Gets the ID of the item that has been selected to edit by the user and populates the jsp file with it's current properties so the user can make changes. "itemDetails" is used to pass the details of the item into the jsp.
        Returns:
        SUCCESS if the fetch from the database was successful. db_error if it was not. permission_error if the user currently logged in is not valid.

      • UpdateItem

        public java.lang.String UpdateItem()
        Update item given the changes the user made in the page generated in the EditItem() method.
        Returns:
        SUCCESS if the update was a success. db_error if it was a fail. permission_error if the user is not valid.
